# Codex Default Rules

## Git Branch Rule
Before committing, check whether the current branch is `main`.
If it is `main`, create and switch to a feature branch before committing.
Never commit directly to `main`.

## Git Push Rule
Before every `git push`, remind the user to:
1. Check pending Prisma migrations with `npx prisma migrate status`.
2. If there are new schema changes, add migrations on the server side in the Vercel dashboard using `npx prisma migrate deploy`.
   Note: `npx prisma migrate deploy` is safe to run multiple times and only applies pending migrations.
3. Ensure `src/generated/prisma/` files are up to date with the schema.

Apply these reminders regardless of which conversation requested the push.
